# VibeStream: Startup Pre-Launch Plan

> **Goal**: Build the next YouTube/Netflix/Twitch for the future. Every decision should be made as if it will scale to 10 million users. Zero monthly AI API costs in launch phase.

## Audit Findings (Senior Dev Review)

### 🔴 Critical Issues
- **Playback 404**: Newly uploaded videos return 404 on the watch page despite existing in the database.
- **Integer 0.9 Mismatch**: The database rejects float values (e.g., 0.9) being inserted into integer columns (likely `quality_score` or `duration`).
- **Sidebar has hardcoded mock users/videos** (`Ninja`, `Valkyrae`, `MrBeast Gaming`) pointing to `/watch/v1`, `/watch/v2` which are 404s.
- **VideoCard**: Thumbnail fallback uses an Unsplash URL — acceptable for dev but must be a local asset or R2-hosted fallback in production.
- **[formatViews](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/utils.ts#5-16) function has a duplicate `if (n >= 1_000_000)` branch** — dead code bug.

### 🟡 UI / UX Notes
- Home page: Clean and solid. **Do not touch.** Featured hero, category bar, and grid are all correct.
- VideoCard: Good design. Minor fix needed: the `CheckCircle2` icon should only appear if `is_verified` is true in the profile (not always shown).
- Profile page needs a full overhaul — still showing mock channels.
- No mobile bottom nav visible on `/watch/[id]` pages.

---

